SELECT  statement:
The select statement is used to select data for databases.It will display all records from in the the column from the table.
WHERE Clause:
Where clause is used to filter records from the table.It extract only those records which fulfill a specific condition.
ORDER BY Keyword
----------------
The order by keyword is used to sort the result in ascending or descending order.
Syntax : Select column_name from Table_name Order by column_name(in consideration) ASC|DESC;   		--> Order By
Note : Default is ascending order.
Select Distinct
---------------
The SELECT DISTINCT statement is used to return only distinct (different) values.			-->Select Distinct
BETWEEN
-------
SELECT * FROM Table_name WHERE Column_name BETWEEN lower_range AND Upper_Range;				-->Between

